  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    public class VelocityCharacterizationRobot
extends IterativeRobot
    Self-contained robot class to characterize a drivetrain's velocity term. Whenever the A button is pressed and held during teleop the robot will carry out a quasi-static velocity characterization as described in Eli Barnett's paper "FRC Drivetrain Characterization" until the button is released. The results (kV, vIntercept, and an R^2 value) are output to the SmartDashboard.
